---
import LandingHeader from "../../components/LandingHeader.astro";
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const repositoryUrl = "https://github.com/nabilrn/MyPaas";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy policy — MyPaas"
  description="How the MyPaas public website and self-hosted instances handle data."
>
  <LandingHeader />
  <main class="policy-page">
    <article class="policy-shell">
      <header>
        <p>Policy</p>
        <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
        <div>
          This policy separates the public MyPaas website from the MyPaas software
          that an operator installs on their own infrastructure.
        </div>
        <span>Effective 13 July 2026</span>
      </header>

      <section>
        <h2>1. Public website</h2>
        <p>
          The public website is a static informational site. As shipped, it does
          not provide accounts, advertising, behavioral analytics, or tracking cookies.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>The theme preference is stored locally in your browser under <code>mypaas-theme</code>.</li>
          <li>The installation copy button writes the displayed command to your clipboard only after you click it.</li>
          <li>The hosting or network provider may process standard request metadata such as IP address, user agent, requested path, and timestamp for delivery and security.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. Self-hosted MyPaas instances</h2>
        <p>
          A MyPaas instance is operated by the person or organization that installs
          it. That operator controls the server, database, domain, access list,
          backups, retention, and connected third-party services.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you use someone else's instance, contact that instance operator about
          access, correction, export, retention, or deletion of your data.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. Data an instance may process</h2>
        <table>
          <thead><tr><th>Category</th><th>Examples and purpose</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><strong>Identity</strong></td><td>GitHub account details and email used for OAuth authentication and whitelist authorization.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Repository configuration</strong></td><td>Repository URL, selected branch, deployment model, ports, and webhook settings used to deploy a project.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Project environment</strong></td><td>Environment keys and values used at runtime. Stored values are encrypted at rest and masked in normal dashboard views.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Operational records</strong></td><td>Deployment history, commit identifiers, build output, runtime logs, status, metrics, and failure context.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Audit records</strong></td><td>Authenticated administration and project actions used for troubleshooting and accountability.</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. Connected services</h2>
        <p>Depending on the operator's configuration, MyPaas interacts with:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>GitHub</strong> for OAuth, repository access, and signed webhook events.</li>
          <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> for DNS, Tunnel ingress, TLS termination, and related network processing.</li>
          <li><strong>Git hosts and container registries</strong> selected by the operator or project configuration.</li>
          <li><strong>Backup storage</strong> configured by the operator for database or application recovery.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Those providers process data under their own terms and privacy policies.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Storage, retention, and deletion</h2>
        <p>
          Instance data is stored on infrastructure controlled by the operator.
          Retention depends on instance configuration, deployment history cleanup,
          project deletion, database backups, and any off-host backup policy.
        </p>
        <p>
          Deleting a project removes tracked project resources through MyPaas, but
          copies may remain in operator-managed backups until those backups expire.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. Security</h2>
        <p>
          MyPaas includes controls such as GitHub OAuth with a database whitelist,
          encrypted environment values, signed webhook verification, local runtime
          port binding, and audit records. These controls reduce risk but do not
          guarantee that an instance is secure.
        </p>
        <p>
          The operator remains responsible for server updates, SSH access, credential
          rotation, backup verification, repository review, and incident response.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7. Questions and changes</h2>
        <p>
          For an installed instance, contact its operator first. For questions about
          the open-source project or this public policy, use the contact method
          published in the <a href={repositoryUrl} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">MyPaas repository</a>.
          Do not post credentials, environment values, or private logs in a public issue.
        </p>
        <p>
          This policy may change when the public website or the MyPaas data model changes.
          The effective date above identifies the current version.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .policy-page {
    min-height: calc(100vh - 4.5rem);
    padding: clamp(3.5rem, 7vw, 6.5rem) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--app-border);
    background: var(--app-bg);
  }

  .policy-shell {
    width: min(calc(100% - 2.5rem), 54rem);
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  header {
    padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--app-border-strong);
  }

  header > p {
    margin: 0 0 0.8rem;
    color: var(--app-accent-strong);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.64rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5.4rem);
    font-weight: 590;
    letter-spacing: -0.058em;
    line-height: 0.98;
  }

  header > div {
    max-width: 42rem;
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--app-muted);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  header > span {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--app-subtle);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
  }

  section {
    padding-top: 3rem;
  }

  h2 {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-size: clamp(1.55rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.036em;
  }

  p,
  li,
  td {
    color: var(--app-muted);
    font-size: 0.87rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 0.8rem 0 1rem;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  li + li {
    margin-top: 0.45rem;
  }

  strong {
    color: var(--app-ink);
    font-weight: 620;
  }

  code {
    padding: 0.12rem 0.3rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--app-border);
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
    background: var(--app-surface-muted);
    color: var(--app-ink);
    font-size: 0.78em;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--app-accent-strong);
    text-underline-offset: 0.2em;
  }

  table {
    width: 100%;
    margin: 1.25rem 0;
    border-collapse: collapse;
  }

  th,
  td {
    padding: 0.8rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--app-border);
    text-align: left;
    vertical-align: top;
  }

  th {
    border-bottom-color: var(--app-border-strong);
    color: var(--app-subtle);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .policy-shell {
      width: min(calc(100% - 1.25rem), 54rem);
    }

    table {
      display: block;
      overflow-x: auto;
    }
  }
</style>
